    "text": "#opentowork \n\nTwo weeks ago, I was impacted by layoffs at Red Hat.\n\nThe 7 years I've spent at Red Hat have been a truly transformative experience for me, both professionally and personally. From the very beginning, I felt a strong connection with Red Hat, and despite the challenges along the way, that connection has endured.\n\nI've always admired the open-source philosophy, and Red Hat has allowed me to become part of various communities even as a non-engineer and contribute in some way, for which I am very grateful.\n\nLastly, I wanted to mention all the hiring managers, engineers, and candidates I had the pleasure to work with, as well as the incredible EMEA TA team. You folks rock!\n\nAfter going through all the stages of the \"Emotional response to change,\" I think I am ready to start pursuing a new job. \n\nHit me up if you know about an open recruitment/communities-related role in an IT company (if it's open source, even better)!",
